<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.10.1.8>
    bibo:endPage "57" ;
    bibo:journal "Phytotaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2010-10-28" ;
    bibo:startPage "49" ;
    bibo:volume "10" ;
    dc:creator "Balete, Danilo S.; Pelser, Pieter B.; Nickrent, Daniel L.; Barcelona, Julie F." ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "Rafflesia verrucosa (Rafflesiaceae), a new species of small-flowered Rafflesia from eastern Mindanao, Philippines" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899824>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899826>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899821> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899824>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A. Newly-opened flower showing verrucose perigone lobes and diaphragm. B. Senescent flower showing persistent sclerenchymatous perigone tissue after warts have fallen off. C. Close-up of the diaphragm and perigone showing dense and prominently raised warts. D. Abaxial surface of the perigone lobe revealing pitted surface beneath corky, cracking and flaking outermost tissue. E. Section through the floral perigone tube showing internal components including the acicular hairs ornamenting the exterior basal 1/3 of the cup-shaped disk, the laminar, interconnected processes of the disk, and the shallowly rugose annulus. F. Top view of the perigone tube interior showing the disk, its processes, and the annulus. A, D–F. Holotype, Balete 17. C. Balete 18. D–F. Specimens in spirit." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4899824/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899826>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A. Longitudinal section through a bud showing both anthers and ovary. B. Cross section through the column neck showing undersurface of disk with anthers in shallow, pubescent sulci, and corona. C. Longitudinal section through an early developing fruit showing slightly lunate ovary. D. Tetrastigma sp., host of R. verrucosa. E. Partially cleared area exposing clusters of buds and senescent flowers attached to the roots of a single host plant. F. Immature bud showing signs of predation. A. Balete 18. B. Holotype, Balete 17. A–B. Specimens in spirit." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4899826/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899821>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Location of known Rafflesia populations in Mindanao. Red circles: extant populations, yellow circle: historical population not observed in recent years." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4899821/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

